newsitem.title: USA: Georgia $257 mln GO bonds won by JP Morgan. [CORRECTED 01:30 GMT 6/8]
newsitem.headline: Georgia $257 mln GO bonds won by JP Morgan. [CORRECTED 01:30 GMT 6/8]

text.p: (Corrects amount in headline and text from $240 mln.)
JP Morgan Securities said Tuesday it won $257 million Georgia general obligation bonds at a net interest cost of 4.7584 percent.
